                            <comment id="14245572" author="stack" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2014 21:48:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=esteban&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;esteban&quot;&gt;Esteban Gutierrez&lt;/a&gt; FYI&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14245585" author="esteban" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2014 22:01:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I&apos;m working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6028&quot; title=&quot;Implement a cancel for in-progress compactions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6028&quot;&gt;HBASE-6028&lt;/a&gt;, my prototype handles only the case to cancel all compactions in progress for now, but I think we can move it as sub task to handle the shell commands that expose this functionality. Does it sounds good for you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=manukranthk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;manukranthk&quot;&gt;Manukranth Kolloju&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14266835" author="manukranthk" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2015 21:51:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the diff for the task : &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.facebook.net/D30993&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.facebook.net/D30993&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14266862" author="esteban" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2015 22:09:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nice work &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=manukranthk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;manukranthk&quot;&gt;Manukranth Kolloju&lt;/a&gt;. I think we went into similar direction, will do some clean up of my patch and lets see if we can merge both changes. I really like the idea of the compactionIdGenerator to keep track of individual compactions and it makes easier to abort (or pause) specific compactions in my current implementation I already have the client code and the ACL code and also the extensions for pbuf.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14266875" author="manukranthk" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2015 22:17:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thats great. We can merge both the patches and expose an Admin endpoint to provide shell commands. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14551239" author="jmspaggi" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 21:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any progress here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14551369" author="manukranthk" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 22:31:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not actively working on this task. Will mark it incomplete. Incase anyone else wants to pick it up, go for it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
